Though they give us leave to practice our rites in cities they control.
I am surprised that our mutual hatred for the Warlocks doesn't make us better bedfellows.
The only good Tremere is the one you kill on the road back to Haqim's bosom.
A pursuit of beauty is luxury and, therefore, wasteful.
I find the sounds of their exsanguination more musical than their ugly gypsy songs.
Their hideous hides a semblance of honor and, this, they are fools.
Their blood brings madness when it stains our lips. Avoid them, lest you be tainted with their derangement.
Untrustworthy and vulgar - but they are nonetheless some of our best employers.
I would almost forsake the tainted blood of animals, but my need is great.
To sup with snakes is to invite their poison to your table.
Whatever gods we shared in the past, we have nothing in common now.

The Assamite vizier bloodline specializes in the study of Thaumaturgy and Middle Eastern magic. Viziers almost never leave the confines of Alamut, and certainly never engage in assassination activities. They instead refine their - and accordingly, the clan's - knowledge of blood magic. Assamite viziers forsake Celerity, instead learning Thaumaturgy as a clan Discipline, but must spend extra blood on Thaumaturgical invocations.  There are not any in this city, so I do not teach it.

We organize ourselves into units similar to packs; these bands are known as falaqi. A falaqi typically consists of two or three Kindred who infiltrate a city and gain a foothold there. Assamites in a city engage in activities common to many Kindred (establishing power bases, cultivating herds), but also weaken rival Kindred through selective assassinations, for we do not see the Sixth Tradition as applying to us.
The Assamites have acquired our appreciable taste for vitae, particularly that of other Kindred.  The clan is easily addicted to the blood of other vampires.

Many Assamites fida'i (newly Embraced apprentices) hail from Asia Minor or northern Africa. Most members of the clan have been involved with assassination, wet work or terrorist activities for some portion of their mortal lives...

You should already know this but fine.  Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Obfuscate is a Discipline that allows vampires to conceal themselves and create some manner of illusions. It is one of the more popular Disciplines practiced by Cainites, and is the source of legends surrounding the ability of vampires to vanish and appear seemingly from nowhere. Quietus is a Discipline that revolves around the idea of inflicting weakness. The downside is that the casters bloodline will always be tainted by the side effects.

Most clan elders make their homes at Alamut, the clan stronghold, which is located high atop a mountain thought to be somewhere in Turkey. Neonates and operatives abroad typically select remote, inaccessible locations to ensure that they receive no unexpected guests.
The Assamites hold all clan in equal contempt. Almost all Assamites remain loners from all the other kindred.
